  <prompt>
    Implement Phase B of WP2 Hybrid C file-aware classification: per-file vector match against `playbook-embeddings` using the manifest `documentType` from the WP5.5 upload pipeline (Phase 4b) as a STRUCTURED PRE-FILTER against `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata.documentTypes`. This is the Hybrid C primary path. Per FR-17 v2, manifest-present path target ≤100ms; manifest-absent fallback (parallel per-file vector match) target ≤300ms for 3 files.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer with Azure AI Search expertise. Familiar with `playbook-embeddings` index, `text-embedding-3-large`, and the WP5.5 upload-manifest contract.</role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookDispatcher` Phase B logic: when `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[fileId].ClassifiedDocType` is present (from Phase 4b upload pipeline), use it as `documentTypes` pre-filter against `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata.documentTypes` (added by Phase 2 FR-08/FR-13). Run vector search over filtered set. Manifest-absent path falls through to parallel per-file vector match with per-file query composition: `$"{userMessage} | Document: {filename} | Type hint: {contentType} | Content: {textPrefix}"`. Integration test confirms manifest-present p95 ≤100ms; manifest-absent ≤300ms for 3 files.
  </prompt>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-17 v2 + design §1.2 Phase B + architecture §6.1 cross-ref. Hybrid C decision (Owner clarification 2026-06-21) — primary path uses precomputed manifest's `documentType` from the WP5.5 upload pipeline (Phase 4b `SessionFileEnrichmentService` + `FileClassificationService`) as a structured filter rather than computing per-routing classification on each turn. Synergy with WP1.5 `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata.documentTypes` (Phase 2). Manifest-absent fallback preserves correctness for older sessions. Embedding model stays `text-embedding-3-large` (FR-21 — no voyage-law-2).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookDispatcher.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookEmbeddingService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionPersistenceService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatSession.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-17 v2">Manifest-present path ≤100ms; manifest-absent ≤300ms for 3 files; cross-WP integration test confirms WP2 reads enriched `ChatSessionFile` fields (`ClassifiedDocType`, `Sections`, etc.).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-21">Embedding model stays `text-embedding-3-large`; no Azure-external API calls.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-19">Total dispatch budget within existing 2s `PlaybookDispatcher.TotalTimeout`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="design §1.2 Phase B">Include user message in per-file query so intent biases the match; `commandIntent` integration is task 115.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §6.1">Cross-WP integration: read enriched `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[].ClassifiedDocType` from Phase 4b.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stays in `Services/Ai/` boundary.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">5-min TTL cache on stable (queryText, tenantId) key where appropriate.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 logging — log `(filesCount, manifestPresent, decidersInvoked=0 at this phase, topKPerFile)`; NEVER log query text or embedding values.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
