  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `PlaybookDispatcher.cs` current state post-111; read `PlaybookEmbeddingService.cs` to understand query composition; read `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[].ClassifiedDocType` shape from Phase 4b.</step>
    <step order="2">Author `Phase B` logic: per-file resolution — given `FileFingerprint` from Phase A + session-side enriched `ClassifiedDocType`, choose path:
      (a) Manifest-present: build filter expression `search.in(documentTypes, '{classifiedDocType}')` against `playbook-embeddings` records (filter on `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata.documentTypes`).
      (b) Manifest-absent: parallel per-file vector match — compose queryText = `$"{userMessage} | Document: {filename} | Type hint: {contentType} | Content: {textPrefix}"`; embed + search topK=5.</step>
    <step order="3">Use `Task.WhenAll` for parallel fan-out across files. Each per-file branch returns top-K candidate playbooks with scores.</step>
    <step order="4">Cache: 5-min TTL keyed on `(tenantId, normalizedQueryText)` for manifest-absent path; manifest-present filtered queries cached on `(tenantId, classifiedDocType, normalizedMessage)`.</step>
    <step order="5">Emit ADR-015 tier-1 telemetry: log `(filesCount, manifestPresent, perFileLatencyMs[], totalLatencyMs, topKCount)`. Never log query content.</step>
    <step order="6">Add unit test asserting manifest-present path: mocked `playbook-embeddings` filter call; assert `documentTypes` filter applied. Add integration test asserting manifest-present p95 ≤100ms (mocked Azure Search; latency from filter overhead only).</step>
    <step order="7">Add integration test asserting manifest-absent fallback ≤300ms for 3 files (mocked embedder; per-call 80-150ms).</step>
    <step order="8">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. All pass.</step>
    <step order="9">Measure BFF publish size; report delta.</step>
    <step order="10">code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 quality gates).</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 112 → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 113.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">PlaybookDispatcher + PlaybookEmbeddingService + ChatSession enriched fields</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Add Phase B logic; update tests</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet build / test / publish</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookDispatcher.cs (Phase B added)</output>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookDispatcherTests.cs (Phase B cases)</output>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/112-bff-publish-delta.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Phase B branches on `ClassifiedDocType` presence; manifest-present path filters on `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata.documentTypes`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Manifest-absent fallback uses parallel per-file vector match.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Embedding model stays `text-embedding-3-large` (FR-21).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Manifest-present test p95 ≤100ms.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Manifest-absent test ≤300ms for 3 files.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Telemetry tier-1 compliant — no query content leakage.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta reported.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">code-review + adr-check exit 0.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Phase B is the Hybrid C primary value-add — the manifest pre-filter dramatically reduces routing cost vs parallel per-file vector match. Falls back gracefully when manifest is absent (e.g., older sessions). Phase C reconciliation (task 113) handles cross-file conflicts when multiple files disagree.
  </notes>

